                            <comment id="13010553" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 04:56:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch also unifies skipBytes checking into skipBytesFully even where we really are only skipping an int&apos;s worth of bytes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010665" author="slebresne" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 13:36:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Small nitpick: it could be nice to add a message to the eof exception saying how many bytes out of how many have been skipped before reaching eof, but that&apos;d require to do a catch and re-throw in the &apos;long&apos; version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13011733" author="jbellis" created="Sun, 27 Mar 2011 05:22:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 adds length information to EOFException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
